How to make a shell Script executable ?

1. Create a new txt file with a .sh extension
2. Add #!/bin/bash on top of it to make it executable.
3. Add command line with full content. 
4. Make command line chmod u+x <filename>.sh to ran file executable.
5. So to run this file, use ./deploy.sh


Use of #!/bin/bash ?

It is used to make file executable


Resolving variables in a shellscript?

By adding environmental variables, arguments and return values, we can resolve variables in a shellscripts.